      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the primary QoI and directly maps to the clinical acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "NIH in mg/dL per 100 L is the regulatory QoI specified in the COU. The CFD post-processing pipeline outputs NIH directly from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated over Lagrangian particle trajectories. QoI alignment is complete. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
